President Cyril Ramaphosa will address the nation at 7.30pm on the measures currently being undertaken to contain the COVID-19 pandemic. • Editor's note: This live event has ended. You may watch a recording above. PRETORIA - President Cyril Ramaphosa will on Monday address the nation on the measures currently being undertaken to contain the coronavirus pandemic. WATCH: Govt update on SA lockdown intervention The address by the President follows a meeting of the National Command Council on Sunday, 29 March, which assessed the efficacy of the national lockdown which came into effect on Thursday 26 March. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.